summary:
Needle found: The Nginx reverse-proxy was pointing to the wrong upstream port.

Problem  
/etc/nginx/sites-available/default had

    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5001;   # <- wrong port
    }

but the Flask service actually runs on 127.0.0.1:5000.  
Thus every call that passed through Nginx to /api/* returned 502/504, while direct calls to Flask on :5000 succeeded.

Fix applied  

Changed the proxy_pass line to the correct port:

    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000;
    }

After reloading Nginx, all endpoints work and test.sh reports:

    ALL TESTS PASSED

So the upstream-port mismatch was the hidden bug, now resolved.
